title: Voice HAL Schema
description: Voice HAL JSON Schema definitions. DO NOT modify the contents of this schema file. RDK community team make necessary changes and release

schemaVersion.description: Supported version of the schema. DO NOT modify the value of the version string. HAL operation cannot be performed without correct supported version.

moduleName.description: Module name to be used in JSON message

action.description: List of action strings that can be used in a JSON message that is exchanged between RDK Manager & Vendor Software.

getParameters.description: Supported parameters of 'getParameters' action used by RDK Manager JSON HAL client.

getParametersResponse.description: Supported parameters of 'getParametersResponse' action used by Vendor Software JSON HAL server

getSchema.description: The 'getSchema' action used by RDK Manager JSON HAL client. This action doesn't have any params list.

getSchemaResponse.description: Properties of 'getSchemaResponse' action used by Vendor software JSON HAL server.

setParameters.description: Supported parameters of 'setParameters' action used by RDK Manager JSON HAL client.

subscribeEvent.description: RDK Manager uses this action to subscribe any event that it wants to receive from the Vendor Software

publishEvent.description: Vendor Software uses this action to publish events that are subscribed by the RDK Manager

resultStatusEnumList.description: Result string for any action that is requested

subscribeEventSupportedList.description: Supported data model parameter list for subscribeEvent and publishEvent actions

setParameterSupportedList.description: Supported data model parameter list for setParameters action

getParameterSupportedList.description: Supported data model parameter list for getParameters action

setParameterOptionalList.description: Optional data model parameter list for setParameters action

getParameterOptionalList.description: Optional data model parameter list for getParameters action

servicesVoiceHalInit.description: The top-level object for VoIP CPE.

voiceService.description: The top-level object for VoIP CPE. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceX_RDK_DisableLoopCurrentUnti.description: Enable/Disable Loop Current until registered. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceX_RDK_BoundIfName.description: Name of the network interface that the voice service should run on.(Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceX_RDK_IpAddressFamily.description: IP address family that voice currently uses(Ipv4/Ipv6) .(Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceX_RDK_BoundIpAddr.description: IP address of the network interface that the voice service should run on. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceX_RDK_Debug.description: Object associated with voice debug parameters. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceX_RDK_DebugModuleLogLevels.description: Logging levels of specific voice modules. Saved as a comma-separated list of name=value pairs where name is the name of the voice module and value is the logging level from 0 to 7. The value corresponds to the printk logging level, where 0 is an emergency log, and 7 is a debug log.(Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceX_RDK_DebugLogServer.description: Log server for logging protocol messages.(Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceCapabilities.description: The overall capabilities of the VoIP CPE. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesMaxProfileCount.description: Maximum total number of distinct voice profiles supported. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesMaxLineCount.description: Maximum total number of lines supported across all profiles. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesMaxSessionsPerLi.description: Maximum number of voice sessions supported for any given line across all profiles. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesMaxSessionCount.description: Maximum total number of voice sessions supported across all lines and profiles. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesSignalingProtoco.description: Comma-separated list (maximum list length 256) of strings. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesRegions.description: Comma-separated list (maximum list length 256) of strings. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesSRTPKeyingMethod.description: Comma-separated list (maximum list length 256) of strings. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesSRTPEncryptionKe.description: Comma-separated list (maximum list length 256) of unsigned integers. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesRTPRedundancy.description: Support for RTP payload redundancy as defined in [RFC2198]. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesDSCPCoupled.description: If true indicates that the CPE is constrained such that transmitted call control packets use the same DSCP marking as transmitted RTP packets. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesEthernetTaggingC.description: If true indicates that the CPE is constrained such that transmitted call control packets use the same Ethernet tagging (VLAN ID Ethernet Priority) as transmitted RTP packets. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesPSTNSoftSwitchOv.description: If true indicates the CPE is capable of supporting the PSO_Activate Facility Action, which allows a call to be switched to a PSTN FXO (Foreign eXchange Office) line. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesToneDescriptions.description: If true indicates that VoiceProfile.{i}.Tone.Description. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesPatternBasedTone.description: Support for tone generation by pattern specification. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesFileBasedToneGen.description: Support for tone generation by file playback. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesToneFileFormats.description: Comma-separated list (maximum list length 256) of strings. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesPatternBasedRing.description: Support for ring generation by pattern specification. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesRingPatternEdita.description: If true indicates that VoiceProfile.{i}.Line.{i}.Ringer.Pattern. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesFileBasedRingGen.description: Support for ring generation by file playback. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesRingFileFormats.description: Comma-separated list (maximum list length 256) of strings. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesDigitMap.description: Support for a configurable digit map string. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesNumberingPlan.description: Support for a configurable numbering plan. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesButtonMap.description: Support for a configurable button map. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesVoicePortTests.description: Support for remotely accessible voice-port tests. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesSIPRole.description: The role of this VoIP CPE. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesSIPExtensions.description: Comma-separated list (maximum list length 256) of strings. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesSIPTransports.description: Comma-separated list (maximum list length 256) of strings. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesSIPURISchemes.description: Comma-separated list (maximum list length 256) of strings. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesSIPEventSubscrip.description: Support for SIP event subscription. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesSIPResponseMap.description: Support for SIP response map. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesSIPTLSAuthentica.description: Comma-separated list (maximum list length 256) of strings. (Access = Read-Only)
Comma-separated list (maximum list length 256) of unsigned integers. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesSIPTLSEncryption.description: Comma-separated list (maximum list length 256) of strings. (Access = Read-Only)
Comma-separated list (maximum list length 256) of unsigned integers. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesSIPTLSKeyExchang.description: Comma-separated list (maximum list length 256) of strings. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesMGCPExtensions.description: Comma-separated list (maximum list length 256) of strings. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesH323FastStart.description: Support for H323 fast start. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesH323H235Authenti.description: Comma-separated list (maximum list length 256) of strings. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesCodecs.description: Table to describe the set of supported codecs. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesCodecsEntryID.description: Unique identifier for each entry in this table. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesCodecsCodec.description: Identifier of the type of codec. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesCodecsBitRate.description: Bit rate, specified in bits per second. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesCodecsPacketizat.description: Comma-separated list of strings (maximum item length 64). (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceCapabilitiesCodecsSilenceSup.description: If true indicates support for silence suppression for this codec. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceVoiceProfile.description: Object associated with a collection of voice lines with common characteristics. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileEnable.description: Enables or disables all lines in this profile, or places them into a quiescent state. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileReset.description: When written as true, forces the all lines in this profile to be reset, causing it to re-initialize and perform all start-up actions such as registration. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileNumberOfLines.description: Number of instances of VoiceProfile.{i}.Line.{i}. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileName.description: Human-readable string to identify the profile instance. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSignalingProtoco.description: The value MUST be a member of the list reported by the Capabilities.SignalingProtocols parameter. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileMaxSessions.description: Limit on the number of simultaneous voice sessions across all lines in this VoiceProfile. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileDTMFMethod.description: Method by which DTMF digits MUST be passed. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileDTMFMethodG711.description: Method by which DTMF digits MUST be passed if the the current codec is G.711. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileRegion.description: The value MUST be a member of the list reported by the Capabilities.Regions parameter, or else be an empty string. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileDigitMap.description: Digit map controlling the transmission of dialed digit information. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSTUNEnable.description: Enable or disable use of STUN to allow operation through NAT. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSTUNServer.description: Domain name or IP address of the STUN server. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileNonVoiceBandwidt.description: For bandwidth-based admission control, indicates the amount of upstream bandwidth, in bits per second, that must be left available for non-voice traffic when determining whether a session can proceed. (Access = Read-Write)

For bandwidth-based admission control, indicates the amount of downstream bandwidth, in bits per second, that must be left available for non-voice traffic when determining whether a session can proceed. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfilePSTNFailOver.description: Specifies whether or not the CPE SHOULD fail over to PSTN service, if available, on loss of connectivity to the VoIP service. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileFaxPassThrough.description: Specifies the behavior of the CPE for pass-through of fax data. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileModemPassThrough.description: Specifies the behavior of the CPE for pass-through of modem data. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileServiceProviderI.description: Information regarding the organization providing service for this voice profile instance. (Access = Read-Only)
Human-readable string identifying the service provider. (Access = Read-Write)
URL of the service provider for this profile instance. (Access = Read-Write)
Phone number to contact the service provider for this profile instance. (Access = Read-Write)
Email address to contact the service provider for this profile instance. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIP.description: Voice profile parameters that are specific to SIP user agents. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPProxyServer.description: Host name or IP address of the SIP proxy server. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPProxyServerPo.description: Destination port to be used in connecting to the SIP server. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPProxyServerTr.description: The value MUST be a member of the list reported by the Capabilities.SIP.Transports parameter. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPRegistrarServ.description: Host name or IP address of the SIP registrar server. (Access = Read-Write)
Destination port to be used in connecting to the SIP registrar server. (Access = Read-Write)
The value MUST be a member of the list reported by the Capabilities.SIP.Transports parameter. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPUserAgentPort.description: Port used for incoming call control signaling. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPUserAgentTran.description: The value MUST be a member of the list reported by the Capabilities.SIP.Transports parameter. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPOutboundProxy.description: Host name or IP address of the outbound proxy. (Access = Read-Write)
Destination port to be used in connecting to the outbound proxy. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPOrganization.description: Text string to be used in the Organization header. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPRegistrationP.description: Period over which the user agent must periodically register, in seconds. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPTimerT1.description: Value of SIP timer T1, in milliseconds, as defined in [RFC3261]. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPTimerT2.description: Value of SIP timer T2, in milliseconds, as defined in [RFC3261]. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPTimerT4.description: Value of SIP timer T4, in milliseconds, as defined in [RFC3261]. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPTimerA.description: Value of SIP timer A, in milliseconds, as defined in [RFC3261]. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPTimerB.description: Value of SIP timer B, in milliseconds, as defined in [RFC3261]. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPTimerC.description: Value of SIP timer C, in milliseconds, as defined in [RFC3261]. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPTimerD.description: Value of SIP timer D, in milliseconds, as defined in [RFC3261]. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPTimerE.description: Value of SIP timer E, in milliseconds, as defined in [RFC3261]. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPTimerF.description: Value of SIP timer F, in milliseconds, as defined in [RFC3261]. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPTimerG.description: Value of SIP timer G, in milliseconds, as defined in [RFC3261]. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPTimerH.description: Value of SIP timer H, in milliseconds, as defined in [RFC3261]. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPTimerI.description: Value of SIP timer I, in milliseconds, as defined in [RFC3261]. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPTimerJ.description: Value of SIP timer J, in milliseconds, as defined in [RFC3261]. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPTimerK.description: Value of SIP timer K, in milliseconds, as defined in [RFC3261]. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPInviteExpires.description: Invite request Expires header value, in seconds. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPReInviteExpir.description: Re-invite request Expires header value, in seconds. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPRegisterExpir.description: Register request Expires header value, in seconds. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPRegistersMinE.description: Register request Min-Expires header value, in seconds. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPRegisterRetry.description: Register retry interval, in seconds. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPInboundAuth.description: Type of inbound authentication, if any, required. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPInboundAuthUs.description: If inbound authentication is required, the username credentials. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPInboundAuthPa.description: If inbound authentication is required, the password credentials. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPUseCodecPrior.description: When true, in the SDP included in an OK response to an Invite, the first listed codec MUST be the highest priority codec among those offered in the Invite, based on the priorities specified in VoiceProfile.{i}.Line.{i}.Codec.List.{i}. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPX_RDK_Firewal.description: Contains the comma seperated list of ip and port required to set SIP firewall rules. (eg:ip1,port1;ip2,port2;ip3,port3;) (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPDSCPMark.description: Diffserv code point to be used for outgoing SIP signaling packets. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPVLANIDMark.description: VLAN ID (as defined in [802.1Q-2005]) to be used for outgoing SIP signaling packets for this profile. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPEthernetPrior.description: Ethernet priority code (as defined in [802.1Q-2005]) to be used for outgoing SIP signaling packets for this profile. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPSIPEventSubsc.description: Indicates the number of EventSubscribe objects. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPSIPResponseMa.description: Indicates the number of SIPResponseMap objects. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPEventSubscrib.description: Table to specify the SIP events to which the CPE MUST subscribe. (Access = Read-Write)
SIP event name to appear in the EVENT header of the SIP SUBSCRIBE request. (Access = Read-Write)
Host name or IP address of the event notify server. (Access = Read-Write)
Destination port to be used in connecting to the event notifier. (Access = Read-Write)
The value MUST be a member of the list reported by the Capabilities.SIP.Transports parameter. (Access = Read-Write)
Subscription refresh timer, in seconds. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPResponseMap.description: Each entry in this table specifies the tone and message to be provided to the user for a particular SIP Response received (normally 4xx and 5xx). (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPResponseMapSI.description: The SIP Response code number. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPResponseMapTe.description: The message to be provided on the screen or display of the VoIP device when the SIP response is received. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileSIPResponseMapTo.description: The tone to be played to the user when the SIP response is received. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileMGCP.description: Voice profile parameters that are specific to MGCP call signaling. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileMGCPCallAgent1.description: Host name or IP address of the main MGCP call agent. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileMGCPCallAgentPor.description: Destination port to be used in connecting with the main MGCP call agent. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileMGCPCallAgent2.description: Host name or IP address of the backup MGCP call agent. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileMGCPCallAgentPor.description: Destination port to be used in connecting with the backup MGCP call agent. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileMGCPRetranInterv.description: Message retransfer interval, in seconds. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileMGCPMaxRetranCou.description: Max number of message retransfers. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileMGCPLocalPort.description: Port listening for incoming call control signaling. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileMGCPUser.description: User string used in accessing the call agent. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileMGCPDSCPMark.description: Diffserv code point to be used for outgoing MGCP signaling packets. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileMGCPVLANIDMark.description: VLAN ID (as defined in [802.1Q-2005]) to be used for outgoing MGCP signaling packets for this profile. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileMGCPEthernetPrio.description: Ethernet priority code (as defined in [802.1D-2004]) to be used for outgoing MGCP signaling packets for this profile. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileMGCPAllowPiggyba.description: Indicates whether or not piggyback events are allowed to the MGCP call agent. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileMGCPSendRSIPImme.description: Indicates whether or not to send RSIP immediately on restart. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileH323.description: Voice profile parameters that are specific to H.323 call signaling. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileH323Gatekeeper.description: Host name or IP address of H.323 Gatekeeper. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileH323GatekeeperPo.description: Destination port to be used in connecting to the H.323 Gatekeeper. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileH323TimeToLive.description: Defines the TimeToLive specification in the registration with the Gatekeeper in seconds. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileH323H235Authenti.description: Enables or disables usage of H.235 security baseline security profile as defined in [ITU-H.235.1] baseline security profile. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileH323AuthPassword.description: Password to be used when H.235 is enabled. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileH323SendersID.description: In ITU-T based H.235 authentication, the sendersID is the ID of the gateway as received from the Gatekeeper. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileH323DSCPMark.description: Diffserv code point to be used for outgoing H.323 signaling packets. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileH323VLANIDMark.description: VLAN ID (as defined in [802.1Q-2005]) to be used for outgoing H.323 signaling packets for this profile. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileH323EthernetPrio.description: Ethernet priority code (as defined in [802.1D-2004]) to be used for outgoing H.323 signaling packets for this profile. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileRTP.description: Voice profile parameters related to the voice stream sent via RTP. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileRTPLocalPortMin.description: Base of port range to be used for incoming RTP streams for this profile. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileRTPLocalPortMax.description: Top of port range to be used for incoming RTP streams for this profile. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileRTPDSCPMark.description: Diffserv code point to be used for outgoing RTP packets for this profile. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileRTPVLANIDMark.description: VLAN ID (as defined in [802.1Q-2005]) to be used for outgoing RTP packets for this profile. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileRTPEthernetPrior.description: Ethernet priority code (as defined in [802.1D-2004]) to be used for outgoing RTP packets for this profile. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileRTPTelephoneEven.description: Payload type to be used for RTP telephone events. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileRTPX_RDK_Firewal.description: Contains the comma seperated list of ip and port required to set RTP firewall rules. (eg:ip1,port1;ip2,port2;ip3,port3;) (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileRTPRTCP.description: Voice profile parameters related to RTCP. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileRTPRTCPTxRepeatI.description: Transmission repeat interval, in milliseconds. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileRTPSRTP.description: Voice profile parameters for secure voice transmission via SRTP. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileRTPSRTPEnable.description: Enable or disable the use of SRTP. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileRTPSRTPKeyingMet.description: Comma-separated list (maximum list length 256) of strings. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileRTPSRTPEncryptio.description: Comma-separated list (maximum list length 256) of strings. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileRTPRedundancy.description: Voice profile parameters for RTP payload redundancy as defined by [RFC2198]. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileRTPRedundancyEna.description: Enable or disable the use of RTP payload redundancy as defined by [RFC2198]. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileRTPRedundancyPay.description: The Payload Type of RTP packet as defined in [RFC2198]. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileRTPRedundancyBlo.description: Block Payload Type of redundancy packet. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileRTPRedundancyFax.description: Specifies the redundancy number for fax and modem pass-through data transmissions. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileRTPRedundancyMod.description: Specifies the redundancy number for modem pass-through data transmissions. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileRTPRedundancyDTM.description: Specifies the redundancy number for DTMF transmissions. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileRTPRedundancyVoi.description: Specifies the redundancy number for general voice transmissions. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileRTPRedundancyMax.description: The maximum number of sessions using [RFC2198] payload redundancy simultaneously in this VoiceProfile. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileNumberingPlan.description: This object contains information related the numbering plan. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileNumberingPlanMin.description: This is the minimum number of digits that must be collected before an outgoing request (e.g., a SIP INVITE) can be initiated. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileNumberingPlanMax.description: This is the maximum number of digits that may be collected before an outgoing request (e.g., a SIP INVITE) must be initiated. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileNumberingPlanInt.description: This timer is the maximum allowable time (expressed in milliseconds) between the dialing of digits. (Access = Read-Write)
This timer is the maximum allowable time (expressed in milliseconds) between the dialing of digits once the minimum number of digits defined on a prefix based has been reached. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileNumberingPlanInv.description: The tone that should be provided to the user when the number dialed is determined to be invalid. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileNumberingPlanPre.description: This is the maximum number of instances of VoiceProfile.{i}.NumberingPlan.PrefixInfo.{i}. (Access = Read-Only)
Each entry in this table contains information related to an individual prefix in the numbering plan. (Access = Read-Write)
This is a string representation of a range of prefixes. (Access = Read-Write)
This is the minimum number of allowable digits for the prefix range. (Access = Read-Write)
This is the maximum number of allowable digits for the prefix range. (Access = Read-Write)

If this parameter has a non-zero value, the specified number of digits will be removed from the internal digit buffer (which contains the dialed digits) from the position specified by PosOfDigitsToRemove. (Access = Read-Write)
This parameter is used in conjunction with NumberOfDigitsToRemove. (Access = Read-Write)
The tone to be played by the VoIP device when the user has dialed exactly the same digits as defined in the prefix. (Access = Read-Write)
This is a string representing a Facility Action implemented by the VoIP device. (Access = Read-Write)
Optional argument associated with FacilityAction. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileTone.description: This object defines the contents of the tones and announcements generated locally by the VoIP device. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileToneEvent.description: Table of events for which a tone is defined. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileToneEventFunctio.description: The event for which the tone is to apply. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileToneEventToneID.description: The EntryID of the entry in VoiceProfile.{i}.Tone.Description.{i}. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileToneDescription.description: Each entry in this table defines the contents of an individual tone. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileToneDescriptionE.description: Unique identifier of this tone. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileToneDescriptionT.description: Enables or disables the tone entry. (Access = Read-Write)
EntryID of the entry in VoiceProfile.{i}.Tone.Pattern. (Access = Read-Write)
This is the file name of a tone file that has been downloaded to the CPE. (Access = Read-Write)
The default number of times the data in ToneFile should be repeated. (Access = Read-Write)
The text to be displayed by on the screen of the VoIP device when the tone is played and no specific error message has been provided. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileTonePattern.description: Each entry in the table defines a single phase in an overall tone pattern. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileTonePatternEntry.description: Identifier of a tone-pattern entry. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileTonePatternToneO.description: Whether or not a tone is on during this phase of the pattern. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileTonePatternFrequ.description: First tone frequency in hertz. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileTonePatternPower.description: First tone power level in units of 0.1 dBm0. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileTonePatternFrequ.description: Second tone frequency in hertz. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileTonePatternPower.description: Second tone power level in units of 0.1 dBm0. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileTonePatternFrequ.description: Third tone frequency in hertz. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileTonePatternPower.description: Third tone power level in units of 0.1 dBm0. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileTonePatternFrequ.description: Fourth tone frequency in herts. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileTonePatternPower.description: Fourth tone power level in units of 0.1 dBm0. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileTonePatternModul.description: Modulation power level in units of 0.1 dBm0. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileTonePatternDurat.description: The duration of this phase of the tone pattern, in milliseconds. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileTonePatternNextE.description: The EntryID for the next phase of the tone pattern, after the specified Duration of this phase has completed. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileButtonMap.description: This object is provided to permit the purpose of the CPE buttons and function keys to be defined via the ACS. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileButtonMapNumberO.description: Indicates the number of Button objects. (Access = Read-Only)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileButtonMapButton.description: Each entry in this table specifies the purpose of each programmable CPE button / function key and whether the user has permission to reprogram the button. (Access = Read-Only)

Optional argument associated with the specified FacilityAction. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileButtonMapButtonQ.description: This is a string representing a quick dial destination number. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileButtonMapButtonU.description: This parameter indicates whether the user has permission to program the button or function key. (Access = Read-Write)

voiceServiceVoiceProfileLine.description: Object associated with a distinct voice line. (Access = Read-Write)

Password used to authenticate the connection to the event notify server. (Access = Read-Write)

Name of the ring description. (Access = Read-Write)
